      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is no standard technology where smart thermostats or fridges analyze audio to detect human emotions and adjust their settings autonomously. Since these devices lack emotional AI capabilities and do not share a central voice assistant trigger, the timing you are observing is likely a result of your conditioned expectation or biological stress response (such as sweating or body heat) subtly affecting the environment. It is highly probable that this is a phantom frequency effect or a psychological pattern, given the absence of documented firmware that links audio analysis to immediate temperature and compressor changes.",
